  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Drafter for Civil & Structural",
  "description": "<p><strong>Drafter (Civil & Structural)</strong></p><p>We are an established Civil & Structural Engineering consultancy involved in Good Class Bungalows projects. We are looking for a responsible and detail-oriented <strong>Drafter</strong> to join our growing team.</p><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Prepare civil & structural drawings, plans, and details based on engineers’ instructions</p></li><li><p>Amend and update drawings according to design changes and authority/consultant comments</p></li><li><p>Ensure drawings comply with project specifications and drafting standards</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with engineers and project team to meet submission deadlines</p></li><li><p>Maintain proper documentation and drawing records<br /><br /><strong>Requirements</strong></p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Diploma / ITE / Technical Certificate in Civil Engineering, Drafting, or related field</p></li><li><p>Proficient in <strong>AutoCAD</strong> (knowledge of BIM / Revit will be an advantage)</p></li><li><p>Minimum <strong>1–3 years</strong> of relevant C&S drafting experience (preferred)</p></li><li><p>Familiar with building structure drawings and detailing</p></li><li><p>Careful, organized, and able to work independently</p></li><li><p>Good teamwork and communication skills</p></li></ul>",
